{{aimai}} {{デフォルトソート:しんるい}}

{{ill|Mankind|de|Menschheit|WD=Q1156970}} refers to the totality of all [[humans]], in a narrower sense the entire [[world population]], or in a more abstract sense the social unity of all people, for example in the case of presumed or actual common decisions or interests of all people.<ref>[//woerterbuchnetz.de/?sigle=DWB&lemma=Menschheit Menschheit] – Eintrag im ''[[Deutsches Wörterbuch|Deutschen Wörterbuch]]'' (von ''[[Jacob Grimm]]'' und ''[[Wilhelm Grimm]]'', im ''[[Wörterbuchnetz]]''); ebenda (noch in [[Brüder Grimm|ihrer]] bevorzugten [[Kleinschreibung]]) unter anderem mit: „art und gesamtheit der menschen“</ref>
== See Also ==
* [[Cradle of Humankind|Cradle of Humankind]] (region where hominization occurred). * [[Human history|Human history]] (from earliest fossil discoveries to the present). * [[Human evolution]] [[Homo sapiens]] * [[World Heritage Site|UNESCO World Heritage]] Heritage of Humanity * [[Human rights|Human rights]] (subjective rights to which everyone is equally entitled). * [[Anthropocene|Anthropocene]] (youngest epoch of earth history, the "age of mankind"). * [[World population|World population]] (number of people on earth)
== References == <references /> {{Draft Categories| [[Category:Philosophical anthropology]] }}
{{Drafts moved from mainspace|date=March 2023}}

