=== Humanity as a Biological Species === As a biological species, “humanity” is a collective term encompassing all entities included in the concept of {{ill|human|de|Mensch|ja|ヒト|zh|人类|12=draft|12=draft}}, whether they are extant species (those still living) or fossil species (those that exist only as fossils)<ref name="britan">{{ill|Encyclopædia Britannica|de|Enzyklopädie Britannica|ja|ブリタニカ百科事典|zh|大英百科全书|12=draft|12=draft}} [Humanity]</ref>; however, there is considerable debate regarding the scope of this inclusion, and even fossil species other than {{ill|Homo sapiens|de|Homo sapiens|ja|ホモ・サピエンス|zh|智人|12=draft|12=draft}} continue to be the subject of ongoing discussion<ref name="britan" />. Common characteristics include the ability to {{ill|bipedalism|de|Bipedalismus|ja|直立歩行|zh|直立行走|12=draft|12=draft}}, a reduction in the size of the {{ill|canine tooth|de|Eckzahn|ja|犬歯|zh|犬齿|12=draft|12=draft}}, and the regression of the {{ill|tail|de|Schwanz|ja|尾|zh|尾巴|12=draft|12=draft}}, among others<ref name="britan" />.
